WEBVTT

00:12.000 --> 00:29.980
7. Now when he had ended all his sayings, in the audience of the people he entered into

00:29.980 --> 00:35.680
Capernaum. And a certain centurion servant, who was dear unto him, was sick, and ready

00:35.680 --> 00:41.360
to die. And when he heard of Jesus, he sent unto him the elders of the Jews, beseeching

00:41.360 --> 00:46.000
him that he would come and heal his servant. And when they came to Jesus, they besought

00:46.000 --> 00:51.700
him instantly, saying, That he was worthy for whom he should do this, for he loveth

00:51.700 --> 00:57.620
our nation, and he hath built us a synagogue. Then Jesus went with them, and when he was

00:57.620 --> 01:03.860
far from the house, the centurion sent friends to him, saying unto him, Lord, trouble not

01:03.860 --> 01:09.960
thyself, for I am not worthy that thou shouldest enter under my roof. Wherefore neither thought

01:09.960 --> 01:15.840
I myself worthy to come unto thee, but say in a word, and my servant shall be healed.

01:16.720 --> 01:22.900
For I also am a man set under authority, having under me soldiers, and I say unto one, Go,

01:22.900 --> 01:29.020
and he goeth, and to another, Come, and he cometh, and to my servant do this, and he

01:29.020 --> 01:34.040
doeth it. When Jesus heard these things, he marveled at him, and turned him about, and

01:34.040 --> 01:39.900
said unto the people that followed him, I say unto you, I have not found so great faith,

01:40.180 --> 01:45.820
no, not in Israel. And they that were sent, returning to the house, found the servant

01:45.820 --> 01:51.840
whole that had been sick. And it came to pass the day after that he went into a city called

01:51.840 --> 01:57.920
Nain, and many of his disciples went with him, and much people. Now when he came nigh to the

01:57.920 --> 02:03.460
gate of the city, behold, there was a dead man carried out, the only son of his mother,

02:03.720 --> 02:09.660
and she was a widow, and much people of the city was with her. And when the Lord saw her,

02:09.660 --> 02:16.640
he had compassion on her, and said unto her, Weep not. And he came and touched the beer,

02:16.640 --> 02:23.260
and they that bear him stood still. And he said, Young man, I say unto thee, Arise. And he that

02:23.260 --> 02:29.720
was dead sat up, and began to speak. And he delivered him to his mother. And there came a

02:29.720 --> 02:35.500
fear on all, and they glorified God, saying, That a great prophet is risen up among us,

02:35.520 --> 02:41.780
and that God hath visited his people. And this rumor of him went forth throughout all Judea,

02:41.780 --> 02:48.000
and throughout all the region round about. And the disciples of John showed him of all these

02:48.000 --> 02:54.560
things. And John, calling unto him two of his disciples, sent them to Jesus, saying, Art thou

02:54.560 --> 03:00.400
he that should come, or look we for another? When the men were coming to him, they said, John

03:00.400 --> 03:06.720
Baptist hath sent us unto thee, saying, Art thou he that should come, or look we for another?

03:07.360 --> 03:12.840
And in that same hour he cured many of their infirmities and plagues, and of evil spirits,

03:13.220 --> 03:18.980
and unto many that were blind he gave sight. Then Jesus answering said unto them, Go your way,

03:19.060 --> 03:24.260
and tell John what things ye have seen and heard. How that the blind see, the lame walk,

03:24.320 --> 03:30.720
the lepers are cleansed, the deaf hear, the dead are raised, to the poor the gospel is preached.

03:31.220 --> 03:34.880
And blessed is he whosoever shall not be offended in me.

03:35.680 --> 03:41.520
And when the messengers of John were departed, he began to speak unto the people concerning John.

03:42.080 --> 03:46.800
What went ye out into the wilderness for to see, a reed shaken with the wind?

03:47.440 --> 03:55.160
But what went ye out for to see, a man clothed in soft raiment? Behold, they which are gorgeously

03:55.160 --> 04:02.260
appareled and live delicately, are in king's courts. But what went ye out for to see, a prophet?

04:02.980 --> 04:08.740
Yea, I say unto you, and much more than a prophet. This is he of whom it is written,

04:09.380 --> 04:15.040
Behold, I send my messenger before thy face, which shall prepare thy way before thee.

04:15.720 --> 04:21.020
For I say unto you, among those that are born of women, there is not a greater prophet than John

04:21.020 --> 04:25.720
the Baptist. But he that is least in the kingdom of God is greater than he.

04:26.500 --> 04:31.340
And all the people that heard him and the publicans justified God being baptized with

04:31.340 --> 04:37.100
the baptism of John. But the Pharisees and lawyers rejected the counsel of God against themselves

04:37.100 --> 04:43.800
being not baptized of him. And the Lord said, Whereunto then shall I liken the men of this

04:43.800 --> 04:49.260
generation? And to what are they like? They are likened to children sitting in the marketplace

04:49.260 --> 04:55.120
and calling one to another and saying, We have piped unto you, and ye have not danced.

04:55.600 --> 05:02.020
We have mourned to you, and ye have not wept. For John the Baptist came neither eating bread

05:02.020 --> 05:08.600
nor drinking wine, and ye say, He hath a devil. The Son of Man is come eating and drinking,

05:08.740 --> 05:14.640
and ye say, Behold, a gluttonous man and a wine-bibber, a friend of publicans and sinners.

05:15.280 --> 05:21.180
But wisdom is justified of all her children. And one of the Pharisees desired him that he

05:21.180 --> 05:25.740
would eat with him, and he went into the Pharisee's house and sat down to meet.

05:26.460 --> 05:33.020
And behold, a woman in the city, which was a sinner, when she knew that Jesus sat at meat

05:33.020 --> 05:39.980
in the Pharisee's house, brought an alabaster box of ointment, and stood at his feet behind him

05:40.780 --> 05:45.600
and began to wash his feet with tears, and did wipe them with the hairs of her head,

05:46.040 --> 05:53.300
and kissed his feet, and anointed them with the ointment. Now when the Pharisee which had

05:53.300 --> 05:58.960
bidden him saw it, he spake within himself, saying, This man, if he were a prophet,

05:59.380 --> 06:06.140
would have known who and what manner of woman this is that toucheth him, for she is a sinner.

06:06.940 --> 06:11.560
And Jesus answering said unto him, Simon, I have somewhat to say unto thee,

06:11.880 --> 06:18.200
and he sayeth, Master, say on. There was a certain creditor which had two debtors,

06:18.360 --> 06:23.980
the one owed five hundred pence and the other fifty, and when they had nothing to pay he

06:23.980 --> 06:31.140
frankly forgave them both. Tell me therefore which of them will love him most. Simon answered and

06:31.140 --> 06:38.500
said, I suppose that he to whom he forgave most. And he said unto him, Thou hast rightly judged.

06:38.980 --> 06:45.100
And he turned to the woman and said unto Simon, Seest thou this woman? I entered into thine house,

06:45.460 --> 06:51.720
thou gavest me no water for my feet. But she hath washed my feet with tears and wiped them

06:51.720 --> 06:57.080
with the hairs of her head. Thou gavest me no kiss, but this woman since the time I came in

06:57.080 --> 07:03.920
hath not ceased to kiss my feet. My head with oil thou didst not anoint, but this woman hath

07:03.920 --> 07:10.840
anointed my feet with ointment. Wherefore I say unto thee, Her sins which are many are forgiven,

07:11.380 --> 07:18.680
for she loved much, but to whom little is forgiven the same loveth little. And he said unto her,

07:18.720 --> 07:24.320
Thy sins are forgiven. And they that sat at meet with him began to say within themselves,

07:24.320 --> 07:34.820
Who is this that forgiveth sins also? And he said to the woman, Thy faith hath saved thee. Go in

07:34.820 --> 07:42.720
peace. Chapter 8. And it came to pass afterward that he went throughout every city and village

07:42.720 --> 07:47.900
preaching and showing the glad tidings of the kingdom of God, and the twelve were with him.

07:48.570 --> 07:54.380
And certain women which had been healed of evil spirits and infirmities, Mary called Magdalene,

07:55.080 --> 08:02.320
out of whom went seven devils, and Joanna, the wife of Chusa, Herod's steward, and Susanna,

08:02.400 --> 08:08.600
and many others, which ministered unto him of their substance. And when much people were gathered

08:08.600 --> 08:16.700
together and were come to him out of every city, he spake by a parable. A sower went out to sow his

08:16.700 --> 08:22.880
seed, and as he sowed, some fell by the wayside, and it was trodden down, and the fowls of the air

08:22.880 --> 08:29.380
devoured it. And some fell upon a rock, and as soon as it was sprung up it withered away because

08:29.380 --> 08:35.990
it lacked moisture. And some fell among thorns, and the thorns sprang up with it and choked it.

08:36.660 --> 08:42.920
And other fell on good ground and sprang up and bare fruit and hundredfold. And when he had said

08:42.920 --> 08:50.980
these things, he cried, He that hath ears to hear, let him hear. And his disciples asked him saying,

08:51.280 --> 08:58.060
What might this parable be? And he said, Unto you it is given to know the mysteries of the kingdom

08:58.060 --> 09:05.580
of God, but to others in parables, that seeing they might not see, and hearing they might not

09:05.580 --> 09:14.320
understand. Now the parable is this, The seed is the word of God. Those by the wayside are they that

09:14.320 --> 09:20.620
hear, then cometh the devil and taketh away the word out of their hearts, lest they should believe

09:20.620 --> 09:28.120
and be saved. They on the rock are they which, when they hear, receive the word with joy, and these

09:28.120 --> 09:35.320
have no root, which for a while believe and in time of temptation fall away. And that which fell

09:35.320 --> 09:42.240
among thorns are they which, when they have heard, go forth and are choked with cares and riches

09:42.240 --> 09:49.700
and pleasures of this life, and bring no fruit to perfection. But that on the good ground are they

09:49.700 --> 09:56.040
which, in an honest and good heart, having heard the word, keep it and bring forth fruit with

09:56.040 --> 10:04.220
patience. No man when he hath lighted a candle covereth it with a vessel, or putteth it under

10:04.220 --> 10:11.820
a bed, but setteth it on a candlestick, that they which enter in may see the light. For nothing is

10:11.820 --> 10:18.780
secret that shall not be made manifest, neither anything hid that shall not be known and come

10:18.780 --> 10:27.320
abroad. Take heed therefore how ye hear, for whosoever hath to him shall be given, and whosoever

10:27.320 --> 10:35.380
hath not from him shall be taken even that which he seemeth to have. Then came to him his mother

10:35.380 --> 10:40.840
and his brethren, and could not come at him for the press. And it was told him by certain which

10:40.840 --> 10:46.640
said, Thy mother and thy brethren stand without, desiring to see thee. And he answered and said

10:46.640 --> 10:54.460
unto them, My mother and my brethren are these which hear the word of God, and do it. Now it

10:54.460 --> 10:59.260
came to pass on a certain day that he went into a ship with his disciples, and he said unto them,

10:59.720 --> 11:06.280
Let us go over unto the other side of the lake. And they launched forth. But as they sailed he

11:06.280 --> 11:11.300
fell asleep, and there came down a storm of wind on the lake, and they were filled with water

11:11.300 --> 11:18.400
and were in jeopardy. And when they came to him and awoke him saying, Master, Master, we perish!

11:19.040 --> 11:24.440
Then he arose and rebuked the wind and the raging of the water, and they ceased, and there was a

11:24.440 --> 11:31.700
calm. And he said unto them, Where is your faith? And they, being afraid, wondered, saying one to

11:31.700 --> 11:38.960
another, What manner of man is this? for he commandeth even the winds and water, and they obey him.

11:39.900 --> 11:45.660
And they arrived at the country of the Gadarenes, which is over against Galilee, and when he went

11:45.660 --> 11:51.620
forth to land there met him out of the city a certain man which had devils long time, and

11:51.620 --> 11:58.280
clothes, neither abode in any house, but in the tombs. When he saw Jesus he cried out and

11:58.280 --> 12:04.240
fell down before him, and with a loud voice said, What have I to do with thee, Jesus,

12:04.500 --> 12:11.980
thou son of God most high? I beseech thee, torment me not. For he had commanded the unclean

12:11.980 --> 12:18.220
spirit to come out of the man. For often times it had caught him, and he was kept bound with

12:18.220 --> 12:24.260
chains and in fetters, and he break the bands, and was driven of the devil into the wilderness.

12:25.440 --> 12:32.720
And Jesus asked him, saying, What is thy name? And he said, Legion, because many devils were

12:32.720 --> 12:38.540
entered into him, and they besought him that he would not command them to go out into the deep.

12:39.520 --> 12:45.580
And there was there and heard of many swine feeding on the mountain, and they besought him

12:45.580 --> 12:51.940
he would suffer them to enter into them, and he suffered them. Then went the devils out of the

12:51.940 --> 12:58.280
man and entered into the swine, and the herd ran violently down a steep place into the lake,

12:58.380 --> 13:04.960
and were choked. When they that fed them saw what was done, they fled and went and told it in the

13:04.960 --> 13:11.900
city and in the country. Then they went out to see what was done, and came to Jesus, and found the

13:11.900 --> 13:19.060
man out of whom the devils were departed, sitting at the feet of Jesus, clothed, and in his right mind,

13:19.400 --> 13:27.080
and they were afraid. They also which saw it told them by what means he that was possessed of the

13:27.080 --> 13:32.620
devils was healed. Then the whole multitude of the country of the Gadarenes round about besought him

13:32.620 --> 13:38.020
to depart from them, for they were taken with great fear, and he went up into the ship and

13:38.020 --> 13:43.700
returned back again. Now the man out of whom the devils were departed besought him that he might be

13:43.700 --> 13:51.220
with him, but Jesus sent him away saying, return to thine own house and show how great things God

13:51.220 --> 13:57.120
hath done unto thee. And he went his way and published throughout the whole city how great

13:57.120 --> 14:04.180
things Jesus had done unto him. And it came to pass that when Jesus was returned the people

14:04.180 --> 14:11.240
gladly received him, for they were all waiting for him. And behold there came a man named Jairus,

14:11.460 --> 14:16.940
and he was a ruler of the synagogue, and he fell down at Jesus's feet, and besought him that he

14:16.940 --> 14:24.000
would come into his house, for he had one only daughter, about twelve years of age, and she lay

14:24.000 --> 14:30.660
a dying. But as he went the people thronged him, and a woman having an issue of blood twelve years,

14:30.660 --> 14:36.420
which had spent all her living upon physicians, neither could be healed of any, came behind him

14:36.420 --> 14:43.060
and touched the border of his garment, and immediately her issue of blood staunched. And

14:43.060 --> 14:50.320
Jesus said, Who touched me? When all denied, Peter and they that were with him said, Master,

14:50.780 --> 14:56.520
the multitude throng thee and press thee, and sayest thou who touched me? And Jesus said,

14:56.520 --> 15:03.700
Somebody hath touched me, for I perceive that virtue is gone out of me. And when the woman saw

15:03.700 --> 15:09.560
that she was not hit, she came trembling, and falling down before him, she declared unto him

15:09.560 --> 15:15.900
before all the people for what cause she had touched him, and how she was healed immediately.

15:16.620 --> 15:22.720
And he said unto her, Daughter, be of good comfort, thy faith hath made thee whole,

15:22.720 --> 15:29.440
go in peace. While he yet spake, there cometh one from the ruler of the synagogue's house,

15:29.500 --> 15:36.200
saying to him, Thy daughter is dead, trouble not the master. But when Jesus heard it, he answered

15:36.200 --> 15:43.820
him saying, Fear not, believe only, and she shall be made whole. And when he came into the house,

15:43.900 --> 15:52.700
he suffered no man to go in, save Peter and James and John, and the father and the mother of the

15:52.700 --> 15:59.920
people wept, and bewailed her. But he said, Weep not, she is not dead, but sleepeth. And they

15:59.920 --> 16:06.780
laughed him to scorn, knowing that she was dead. And he put them all out, and took her by the hand,

16:07.020 --> 16:16.140
and called, saying, Maid, arise. And her spirit came again, and she arose straightway, and he

16:16.140 --> 16:22.060
commanded to give her meat. And her parents were astonished, but he charged them that they should

16:22.060 --> 16:28.460
tell no man what was done. End of chapters 7 and 8.

